comments.message:
I think I'd prefer the logic inverted for this.

if (version < 2)
{
   ... stuff without the field
}
else
{
   ... stuff with the field.
}

Too bad there isn't an easy way to implement this with a case + fall-through... or is there?  If you switch the order so retryAttempts is added to the archive first then:

retryAttempts = BOOT_COUNT_MAX_ALLOWED;
switch (version) 
{
    case 2:
        archive(retryAttempts);
        // need some magic allow-fallthrough comment.

    case 1:
        archive(reqTranState, bootProgress, osState);
        break;
}
